Overview

  This Eclipse plugin provides a UI for the {{{../legstar-schemagen/index.html} XML Schema generation feature}} of LegStar.

  LegStar Schemagen translates COBOL constructs into XML Schema elements. The resulting XML schema is extented
  with COBOL specific annotations. For instance, a COBOL sentence such as:
  
---------------------------------------------
  10 REPLY-ITEMSCOUNT        PIC 9(8) COMP-3.        
---------------------------------------------
  
  Would be translated to:
  
+-------------------------------+
     <xs:element name="ReplyItemscount">
       <xs:annotation>
         <xs:appinfo>
         <cb:cobolElement levelNumber='10' cobolName='REPLY-ITEMSCOUNT'
                          type='PACKED_DECIMAL_ITEM' picture='9(8)'
                          usage='PACKED-DECIMAL' byteLength='5'
                          signed='false' totalDigits='8'/>
         </xs:appinfo>
       </xs:annotation>
       <xs:simpleType>
         <xs:restriction base="xs:unsignedInt">
         <xs:minInclusive value='0' fixed='true'/>
         <xs:maxInclusive value='99999999' fixed='true'/>
         </xs:restriction>
       </xs:simpleType>
     </xs:element>
+-------------------------------+
  
  The COBOL annotation language is important because of the <impedance mismatch> between the XML schema
  language and the COBOL language. The use of annotations preserves information such as:
  
    * Numeric types (Packed decimals do not exist in XML schema for instance) 

    * Number of digits (COBOL enforces controls on the number of digits while XML schema does not)
    
    * Size of character strings (Strings have fixed sizes in COBOL)  
    
    * <Occurs Depending On> COBOL sentences relate an array with another element giving the actual size
 
  
  See the {{{xml/legstarschemagen.xsd} COBOL annotation XML Schema}} page for more information on the
  COBOL annotation language used by Schemagen.

  For answers to common questions about LegStar, see the {{{faq.html} FAQ}}.
